In the infusion method, JCO2(inf) was determined based on CO2 input flow rate, using the following equation:
\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ {\mathrm{JCO}}_{2\left(\operatorname{inf}\right)}\left(\mathrm{mL}/\min \right)={\mathrm{QCO}}_2\times \left({\mathrm{p}}_{\mathrm{in}}{\mathrm{CO}}_{2\left(\mathrm{ref}\right)}/{\mathrm{p}}_{\mathrm{in}}{\mathrm{CO}}_{2\left(\mathrm{inlet}\right)}\right) $$\end{document}JCO2infmL/min=QCO2×pinCO2ref/pinCO2inlet

QCO2 values are referred to in mL/min under normal conditions (0 °C, 1013 mbar) and are re-calculated where appropriate, applying the ideal gas equation:
\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ Q(T)={\mathrm{QCO}}_2\times \left(273.15+T\right)/273.15 $$\end{document}QT=QCO2×273.15+T/273.15

In addition, using the more commonly utilized blood gas analysis method, the normalized CO2 removal rate (JCO2(BGA)) was determined according to the following equation:
\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ {\mathrm{JCO}}_{2\left(\mathrm{BGA}\right)}\left(\mathrm{mL}/\min \right)=\left({V}_{\mathrm{m}}\times {Q}_{\mathrm{B}}\times \Big[{\mathrm{ctCO}}_{2\left(\mathrm{inlet}\right)}-{\mathrm{ctCO}}_{2\left(\mathrm{outlet}\right)}\right]\Big)\times \left({\mathrm{p}}_{\mathrm{in}}{\mathrm{CO}}_{2\left(\mathrm{ref}\right)}/{\mathrm{p}}_{\mathrm{in}}{\mathrm{CO}}_{2\left(\mathrm{inlet}\right)}\right) $$\end{document}JCO2BGAmL/min=Vm×QB×[ctCO2inlet−ctCO2outlet)×pinCO2ref/pinCO2inlet
